From ea9848405e4ca8ecfd807a49f4de23980a5cbc18 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kavita Kavita <kkavita@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 21 Jul 2025 09:16:10 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 11/13] Add Support for Handling Link Reconfiguration Updates 
 from Kernel

Add support for processing the NL80211_CMD_ASSOC_MLO_RECONF event from the
Kernel. This event includes information about added links and the link
reconfiguration response frame from the AP MLD. The event can be triggered
by either supplicant or driver-initiated link reconfiguration updates.

This commit also adds support for the installation of group keys
(e.g., GTK, IGTK, BIGTK etc) received with the link reconfiguration
response frame for the newly added links.

For removed links, the existing NL80211_CMD_LINKS_REMOVED event is used,
requiring no additional changes in the supplicant for both supplicant and
driver-initiated link reconfiguration updates.

Signed-off-by: Kavita Kavita <kkavita@qti.qualcomm.com>
